The Offer

Become a shareholder in a fast growth edtech taking Australia and the world by storm. Take advantage of a limited offer to invest from $5,000 minimum through VentureCrowd and reap the benefits of buying in at a pre-money valuation of $10M, with a company that’s grown by 5X over the last two years and that’s projected to triple in value over the next three years. With $300,000 already committed weeks before the round opening, this is your opportunity to grow your portfolio and wealth while supporting the growth of others via the smart-tech Elladex platform.

Growth Strategy

  • Elladex has grown by over 200% over the last three months alone
  • Elladex works with large and medium-size companies investing in memberships for their female employees, companies with diversity and inclusion goals and those that want to meet their ESG targets

Use of Funds and Exit Strategy

Funds will be used to achieve the following in 18 months:

  • Grow ARR from ~$400k p/a to $2.1M over 18 months
  • Acquire 27,000 total users and covert 7,000 to premium users
  • Onboard 185 Executive Circle members
  • Further develop our super-app technology with advancements in machine learning
  • Invest in content and scalable marketing
  • Expand our operations globally with a focus on India followed by the US after achieving our 18 month goals

Elladex is projected to be valued at $30m in the next 3 years, based on Australian operations alone. As a fast-growing edtech with a global presence and strong time-delay barrier to entry for other competitors thanks to our comprehensive native content library, super-app integration of 3 pillars and machine learning, Elladex provides strong exit capitalisation opportunities for our investors.

Shareholders have many profitable exit opportunities with large media companies investing in the space of female social learning communities, financial institutions investing thanks to Elladex’s financial literacy education, and other large edtech players who want access to Elladex’s technology, database and synergies. These are just some of the short-to-medium term exit opportunities, while Elladex works towards an IPO.

componentInstanceProperties.value:
What is Elladex?

Elladex is the Spotify of personal and professional development combined with an in-built mentor marketplace and executive coaching program for women who want more.

90% of women want access to personal growth, career development and financial wellness learning and mentoring, but struggle to find the time and energy to get their needs met.

Elladex empowers professional women at any stage of their career or business through three pillars of development:

  • Elladex’s mobile super-app and digital network for women delivering bite-sized personalised learning, guided meditation, and social sharing features.
  • A built-in mentor marketplace for easy mentor meetings with integrated calendar bookings, payments, voice and video calls.
  • Elladex’s Executive Circle program and alumni network for women in senior positions wanting to progress to executive roles with a higher professional profile.

Elladex’s integrated super-app is a first to market, has a 25,000-strong community following already and is championed by ambassadors including Tracey Spicer, Jana Pittman and Catherine Fox.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Problem and Market

Women experience many gender-based gaps that hold them back socially, economically and professionally—the gender pay gap, the leadership gap, the superannuation gap and the wealth gap.

Elladex works to address these gaps by identifying women’s individual challenges as a result of these issues. Research and engagement with our 25,000-strong community found that over 90% of women want access to mentors and are willing to pay over $100 per session.

We’ve also found that women want one place to access their learning needs rather than having to use up to three different apps. They want access to wellness content, to invest in their career and leadership growth, and to learn how to be financially independent. With over 33 million women across Australia and the US who work in a professional role, the penetration of the serviceable addressable market in Australia alone would equate to over $680M in annual recurring revenue.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Elladex Solution

Elladex’s super-app is a digital community for women to connect, learn and grow in one platform. Through the app women get access to over 100 proprietary micro-learning courses spanning 20 learning topics delivered through +10,000 minutes of video learning and 500+ articles of written content. The portfolio also has a growing list of exclusive PowerClasses delivered by celebrity and industry leading instructors. Personalised learning playlists are curated for each member based on their career stage and personal goals. Members can interact with the app using a freemium or premium subscription for $19 per month.

Built into the super-app is the mentoring marketplace. A 2-sided marketplace where members can seamlessly book and engage with mentors all in-app. Sessions range from $100 to $300 of which Elladex takes a 10% transaction fee. Mentors pay a $9.99 per week SaaS fee to use the SaaS tool which manages calendaring, payments and video conferencing.

Elladex’ Executive Circle program powers the executive careers of women in senior roles. The 12-month program is delivered digitally and includes fortnightly workshops and round table sessions, career development planning, psychometric testing, and VIP networking events. The program is delivered in partnership with Deakin University and graduates receive a 50% learning credit towards an MBA with Deakin.

Competitive Advantage

Elladex has developed a substantial first-mover advantage with an all-in-one digital platform and large proprietary native content library. The business will seek to capitalise on this by strengthening its brand and content portfolio while growing the network of members and mentors.

  • A growing member and mentor base strengthens the social learning aspect of the platform, increasing network effects.
  • Market leading content portfolio and expanding library of celebrity training and PowerClasses.
  • Partnering with Australian universities.
  • Elladex enables large B2B clients to fulfill their Diversity and Inclusion plus Environmental Social Governance targets but offering their workforce wellness, career growth and financial literacy in one platform.

Fees

Investors invest through a VentureCrowd Trust, which VentureCrowd manages as a single asset. We charge an annual management fee to investors, payable on exit and we only charge a performance fee where an exit delivers profit, thereby aligning ourselves with investor outcomes.

  • Contribution Fee: 1.1% This is the fee charged by the Trustee for establishing the Trust and the purchasing entity, structuring the overall investment and raising capital by issuing Units. Payable upon acceptance of your investment by the Trustee.
  • Management Fee: 1.65% per annum (charged on conversion or exit).
  • Performance Fee: 20% of the profit. We only charge a performance fee on conversion or exit.

Risks

Investing in private companies is risky. Issuers using this facility include new or rapidly growing ventures. Investment in these types of ventures is speculative and carries high risks. You may lose your entire investment, and you should be in a position to bear this risk without undue hardship. Even if the company is successful, the value of your investment and any return on the investment could be reduced if the company issues more shares. Your investment is unlikely to be liquid. This means you are unlikely to be able to sell your shares quickly or at all if you need the money or decide that this investment is not right for you. Even though you have remedies for misleading statements in the offer document or misconduct by the company, you may have difficulty recovering your money. There are rules for handling your money. However, if your money is handled inappropriately or the person operating this platform becomes insolvent, you may have difficulty recovering your money. Ask questions, read all information given carefully, and seek independent financial advice before committing yourself to any investment.
